  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law in the United States, money laundering is a serious crime with severe penalties. The specific penalties depend on the circumstances of the offense, including the amount of money involved and the nature of the underlying criminal activity. Here are the key penalties for money laundering:\n\n1. **Imprisonment**:\n   - Individuals convicted of money laundering can face up to **20 years in federal prison** for each offense.\n   - If the money laundering is connected to a violation of the **Bank Secrecy Act** or certain other financial crimes, the maximum sentence can increase to **10 years per violation**.\n\n2. **Fines**:\n   - Monetary **fines** can be substantial. For individuals, fines can reach up to **$500,000 or twice the value of the property involved in the transaction, whichever is greater**.\n   - For **organizations**, fines can be up to **$1 million or twice the value of the property involved**.\n\n3. **Civil Penalties**:\n   - In addition to criminal penalties, individuals and organizations may face **civil penalties**, including forfeiture of property involved in or derived from the money laundering activity.\n   - Civil fines can be up to the value of the laundered funds or $10,000, whichever is greater.\n\n4. **Asset Forfeiture**:\n   - The government can seize and **forfeit any property, funds, or assets** involved in the money laundering scheme, including bank accounts, real estate, vehicles, and other valuables.\n\n5. **Other Consequences**:\n   - Conviction for money laundering can result in the **loss of professional licenses**, reputational damage, and other collateral consequences.\n   - Money laundering charges often accompany other charges (e.g., drug trafficking, fraud), which can result in additional penalties.\n\nThe severity of the penalties underscores the federal government's commitment to combating money laundering and related financial crimes. For specific cases, the exact penalties will depend on factors such as the defendant\u2019s criminal history, the scope of the scheme, and whether the defendant cooperates with authorities.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
